{"TopicId":171162,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"A clock that will last for 10,000 years.","CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T00:19:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T00:19:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther ipsEmbeddedOther_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1849951359\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/JeffBezos/status/965957024109379602\u0022 style=\u0022height:532px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://longnow.org/clock/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://longnow.org/clock/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T00:46:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis extra \u00220\u0022 is\u00A0cute:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nABOUT LONG NOW\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe Long Now Foundation was established in 01996* to foster long-term thinking and responsibility in the framework of the next 10,000 years.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T00:52:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAparrently there\u0027s a second clock planned for Nevada:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://longnow.org/clock/nevada/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://longnow.org/clock/nevada/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/VTUrdizRZyw?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T00:54:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n...\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#1c2022;font-size:16px;text-align:left;\u0022\u003Epowered by day/night thermal cycles, synchronized at solar noon, ...\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about the tides ? They\u0027re pretty accurate that in some parts of this country they\u0027re used to tell when New Moon occurs...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/odX81LsE5RY?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut yeah, no clock tells years I guess !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T00:59:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy September 27th 2071 long extinct trilobites (or direct descendents of) will be found in the deep waters of the seas possibly, but not exclusively, around underwater hydrothermal vents.\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe long now foundation has many interesting branches.\u00A0 For example, they have Rosetta and PanLex, to create a global language datbase, de-extinction, and the Long Bets division, which has bets about the future(money donated to chairities) that rnage from short term economic predictions to what I just quoted.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T07:54:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s got to be some reasonable middle ground between thinking about your next meal and thinking about 10,000 years from now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T07:58:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk cool. See if it lasts, and doesn\u0027t get destroyed by post-apocalypse rebels who scavange for precious metals of some sort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T09:08:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300617\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519199889\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk cool. See if it lasts, and doesn\u0027t get destroyed by post-apocalypse rebels who scavange for precious metals of some sort.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEasy to prevent, just build a technology-worshipping cult that sees the clock as a literal God, throw a few sinners into its inner workings, that sort of thing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n***\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the Guardian yesterday there was this headline:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch1 style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#121212;padding:0px;\u0022\u003E\nDavid Davis: Brexit will not plunge Britain into \u0027Mad Max dystopia\u0027\n\u003C/h1\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe first thing I thought: HOLY HOT DANG, THAT WAS A \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003ERISK\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E!?!?!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Antstar","CreatedById":174784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T09:54:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust LOL.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen I first went to uni, we were shown around the place. I remember being shown the \u0022unbreakable clock\u0022 build by a group of engineers. Apparently it took about 5 years before another group of engineers figured out how to break it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe rate of change in our culture is higher than ever in history, and accelerating.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI put my money on it lasting less than 250 years. It only takes one generation to rip it down, it takes every generation to preserve it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T10:07:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd people run after a new silly idea every other day. As if it had any impact on real life.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/74091-p1t1o/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002274091\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/74091-p1t1o/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@p1t1o\u003C/a\u003E, English tabloids like Sun and Express reported people in fear and hundreds of earthquakes on La Palma island (where i live, right above the quakes on the western slope). Tourism here was concerned about such sort of \u0022information\u0022 and i can tell you the Spaniards are extremely relaxed usually.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe truth: a swarm of earthquakes mag 1 to 2.5 in the upper mantle (depth 25-30km) since last November may be a hint of a slow intrusion of highly viscous material. Period. No panic, people here where informed by the usual news channels and frankly, microquakes are not unusual. Nothing could be sensed, it only got to our knowledge because the southern part of La Palma, being regarded as an active volcano, is watched over by several seismic stations, laser measurement of ground movement and gps stations for the same reason.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300414\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519174493\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about the tides ? They\u0027re pretty accurate that in some parts of this country they\u0027re used to tell when New Moon occurs...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, the other way round, the movement of celestial bodies (mainly moon, sun, Jupiter) is used to determine time and height of the tides and the connected streams :-) More info e.g. via Admiralty Tide Tables (ATT) which are sort of a nautical standard.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-02-21T10:10:27Z\u0022 title=\u002202/21/2018 10:10  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"p1t1o","CreatedById":74091,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T10:35:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300673\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519207658\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n24 minutes ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd people run after a new silly idea every other day. As if it had any impact on real life.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI dunno, its stated purpose is to stimulate long-term thinking, which personally I think is a good idea, whether the clock lasts or not.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPeople get all excited about space travel and colonising Mars, and\u00A0they want it NOW or in the next coupla decades. Whereas in reality it will involve some real long-term thinking, maybe not on the 10-millenia scale, but longer than we are used to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T11:10:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, yeah, but the longest theoretically possible thinking term is a human life time minus something at the beginning and at the end. Irl the term is much shorter and connected to a reporting term, an election period or in general to the momentary circumstances.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn this special case: Bezos is short term thinking, bringing a brand and a name into the headlines. He would be really long term thinking if he built schools and colleges for example in central Africa from his money instead, to give moar opportunities to the next generation.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey, this is only my personal opinion, which might be totally wrong and leaves room for others :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DAL59","CreatedById":180784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T11:59:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300666\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519206850\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Antstar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Antstar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI put my money on it lasting less than 250 years. It only takes one generation to rip it down, it takes every generation to preserve it \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is designed to not need mantainance.\u00A0 The only risk is scrap metal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe should have made it count down, to confuse future generations.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Antstar","CreatedById":174784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T14:34:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300718\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519214378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt is designed to not need mantainance.\u00A0 The only risk is scrap metal.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScrap metal is one possibility. Or perhaps future America will find the idea of thinking long term culturally disgusting. Perhaps they will decide that the first 30 years of the third millennium were the most shameful and remove all traces of it from the Earth. Or a nationwide cult of technological regression. Or a hundred other things I can\u0027t even imagine...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300718\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519214378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe should have made it count down, to confuse future generations.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyup \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T14:40:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300673\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519207658\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, the other way round, the movement of celestial bodies (mainly moon, sun, Jupiter) is used to determine time and height of the tides and the connected streams :-) More info e.g. via Admiralty Tide Tables (ATT) which are sort of a nautical standard.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, if you found a correlation, you can continue track it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300718\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519214378\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe should have made it count down, to confuse future generations.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr count up then running out and simply overflow.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s some pretense before that overflow...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222012_Poster.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022385\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/d/dd/2012_Poster.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022259\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-02-21T14:50:57Z\u0022 title=\u002202/21/2018 02:50  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheSaint","CreatedById":70033,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T17:10:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome numbskull just \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/19/world/asia/terra-cotta-warrior.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ebroke a thumb off of one of the terracotta warriors\u003C/a\u003E because he thought it would make a cool souvenir. Unless they hire 24-hour security, the 10,000 Year Clock isn\u0027t going to make it two weeks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T19:01:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes it have alarm clock?\u003Cbr\u003E\nJust not to forget to wind them in 12018.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-02-21T19:02:03Z\u0022 title=\u002202/21/2018 07:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T20:02:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300955\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171162\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519233059\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002270033\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheSaint\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, TheSaint said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome numbskull just \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/19/world/asia/terra-cotta-warrior.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ebroke a thumb off of one of the terracotta warriors\u003C/a\u003E because he thought it would make a cool souvenir. Unless they hire 24-hour security, the 10,000 Year Clock isn\u0027t going to make it two weeks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat ? They should chop off his thumb !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry, archaeologist\u0027s short circuit reaction ... :-/\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-02-21T20:04:39Z\u0022 title=\u002202/21/2018 08:04  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheSaint","CreatedById":70033,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-21T20:40:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere\u0027s one in every crowd. Which is why the clock is doomed. Some self-centered moron will come along who decides that his need to feel special is greater than their need to keep the clock running.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","C